# IAP (Identity-Aware Proxy) Setup Guide

## Overview

IAP protects internal services (ArgoCD, Grafana, etc.) with Google OAuth authentication. Only users from your allowed domain can access these services.

## Why Manual Setup is Required

**Google deprecated the IAP OAuth Admin APIs** in July 2025. OAuth clients can no longer be created programmatically via Terraform/Pulumi/gcloud. You must create them manually in the GCP Console.

> The APIs will be permanently shut down on **March 19, 2026**.

## How It Works

```
User → Browser → Traefik → iap-auth middleware → OAuth2 Proxy → Protected Service
                              ↓
                    If not authenticated:
                    Redirect to Google OAuth
```

## Setup Instructions

### Step 1: Create OAuth Credentials in GCP Console

1. Go to [GCP Console → APIs & Services → Credentials](https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials)
2. Select your project ({{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-staging or {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-production)
3. Click **"Create Credentials"** → **"OAuth client ID"**
4. Application type: **"Web application"**
5. Name: `{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }} IAP Staging` (or Production)

### Step 2: Configure OAuth Client

**Authorized JavaScript origins:**

For **staging**:

```
https://staging.{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}
```

For **production**:

```
https://{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}
```

**Authorized redirect URIs:**

For **staging**:

```
https://traefik.staging.{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}/oauth2/callback
https://grafana.staging.{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}/oauth2/callback
https://k8s-dashboard.staging.{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}/oauth2/callback
https://argocd.staging.{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}/oauth2/callback
```

For **production**:

```
https://traefik.{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}/oauth2/callback
https://grafana.{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}/oauth2/callback
https://k8s-dashboard.{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}/oauth2/callback
https://argocd.{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}/oauth2/callback
```

6. Click **"Create"**
7. Download the JSON file or copy the **Client ID** and **Client Secret**

### Step 3: Add Credentials to Secrets JSON

Add `iap-credentials` to your secrets file:

```bash
# Edit the appropriate environment file
vim src/_secrets/staging.json    # or production.json
```

Add this section (generate cookie-secret with `openssl rand -base64 32`):

```json
{
  "iap-credentials": {
    "client-id": "YOUR_CLIENT_ID.apps.googleusercontent.com",
    "client-secret": "GOCSPX-your-secret",
    "cookie-secret": "YOUR_32_BYTE_BASE64_COOKIE_SECRET="
  }
}
```

### Step 4: Sync Secrets to Pulumi Config

```bash
cd /workspaces/{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}/iac/pulumi

# For staging:
./scripts/pulumi-secret-set.sh -e staging

# For production:
./scripts/pulumi-secret-set.sh -e production
```

### Step 5: Deploy IAP

```bash
pulumi up -s staging  # or production
```

Pulumi will now deploy the OAuth2 Proxy and iap-auth middleware.

## Verification

After deployment, try accessing a protected service:

1. Go to https://argocd.staging.{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}
2. You should be redirected to Google sign-in
3. After signing in with a @{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }} account, you should see ArgoCD

## Troubleshooting

### "redirect_uri_mismatch" error

- Check that all redirect URIs are added to the OAuth client
- Ensure there are no trailing slashes
- Wait a few minutes for changes to propagate

### "access_denied" error

- Verify your email domain is in the allowed list (`{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}`)
- Check the `allowedMembers` config in Pulumi

### OAuth2 Proxy pods not starting

- Check if ExternalSecret synced: `kubectl get externalsecret -n {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}`
- Check if secret exists: `kubectl get secret iap-oauth-credentials -n {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}`
- Check GCP Secret Manager has values: `gcloud secrets versions list iap-credentials-client-id --project={{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-staging`

## Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                        GCP Secret Manager                        │
│  iap-credentials-client-id, iap-credentials-client-secret,      │
│  iap-credentials-cookie-secret                                   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼ (ExternalSecret sync)
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    K8s Secret: iap-oauth-credentials             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                       OAuth2 Proxy Deployment                    │
│  - Reads credentials from secret                                 │
│  - Handles Google OAuth flow                                     │
│  - Sets X-Auth-Request-* headers                                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              Traefik Middleware: iap-auth (ForwardAuth)          │
│  - Calls OAuth2 Proxy /oauth2/auth for every request            │
│  - If 401, redirects to Google sign-in                          │
│  - If 200, forwards request with auth headers                   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Configuration Reference

### Secrets JSON Structure

Add to `src/_secrets/staging.json` or `src/_secrets/production.json`:

```json
{
  "iap-credentials": {
    "client-id": "YOUR_CLIENT_ID.apps.googleusercontent.com",
    "client-secret": "GOCSPX-your-secret",
    "cookie-secret": "YOUR_32_BYTE_BASE64_COOKIE_SECRET="
  }
}
```

Generate a cookie secret:

```bash
openssl rand -base64 32
```

### Environment Config (Pulumi.{env}.yaml)

```yaml
{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}:security:
  iap:
    enabled: true
    supportEmail: admin@{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}
    allowedMembers:
      domain: {{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }}
    protectedServices:
      - traefik
      - grafana
      - k8s-dashboard
      - argocd
    oauth2ProxyVersion: "v7.5.1"
    cookieDomain: .staging.{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }} # or .{{ .Project.Metadata.Domain }} for prod
    # ... other settings
```

## Notes

- Cookie secret should be 32+ bytes, base64 encoded (generate with `openssl rand -base64 32`)
- All IAP credentials are stored in GCP Secret Manager and synced to K8s via ExternalSecret
- If `iap-credentials` is not configured, Pulumi will skip IAP deployment with a warning
- Services remain accessible without auth until IAP is configured
